  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nobody Should Go Blind JUST Because They Are Poor!</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">73 year old Philemon lived in fear, the slightest sound or touch was enough to put him over the edge, he was as jumpy as a meerkat because he could not see. It was only Anna his wife that could put him at ease when we tested his eyes, she had to softly whisper in his ear all the way. Man, the joy on his face when he could see Anna&apos;s face for the 1st time in 19 years. It brought involuntary streams of tears to the teams eyes. 80% of blindness is preventable....</narrative>
  </description>
